<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1399,1638,2028]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
This species was described based on an undetermined number of specimens of both sexes collected by J. Ogilvie at 
<collectingCountry box="[308,423,1678,1704]" name="Barbados" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Barbados</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell" box="[431,627,1678,1705]" firstAuthor="Cockerell" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="142" refId="ref20306" refString="Cockerell T. D. A. 1939. Bees of the genus Centris from Barbados, B. W. I. The Entomologist 72: 142." type="journal article" year="1939">Cockerell (1939)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the type of the species was a male.A male specimen belonging to the type series is currently housed at 
<collectionCode box="[816,927,1719,1745]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
and was labeled as type by Cockerell himself. Another male of the type series was found at 
<collectionCode box="[828,918,1760,1786]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and was labeled by Cockerell as cotype. The female specimen mentioned in the original description was not found. The male 
<typeStatus box="[1204,1307,1799,1825]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
housed at 
<collectionCode box="[218,329,1840,1866]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
has the following data label: [circular label with red-rimmed margin] Type [printed]\ B.M. TYPE Hym. [printed] 17B.928 [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ckll." authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1939" box="[733,1034,1880,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbadensis">
<emphasis box="[733,969,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Centris barbadensis</emphasis>
Ckll.
</taxonomicName>
Type [handwritten]\ 
<collectingCountry box="[1280,1395,1880,1906]" name="Barbados" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Barbados</collectingCountry>
. 27.4.38. (J. Ogilvie) [handwritten]\ Type in Banks Coll. [printed]. The male 
<typeStatus box="[1082,1183,1921,1947]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">paratype</typeStatus>
housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1309,1399,1921,1947]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
